# ORIG TITLE    At least 30 dead in India bus crash . 
# ORIG CONTENT  At least 30 people have been killed and dozens injured after a bus skidded off a road and plunged into a river in a mountainous area of northern India. The accident happened near Kullu, a popular resort, in Himachal Pradesh state. The bus was partially submerged in the river Beas, forcing rescuers to use boats. Emergency crews say they fear other victims might have been washed away. A similar crash in the area less than a month ago killed 12 people. 
